    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.8.0-dev+2-g08a144912c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.25.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR neovim-git\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean` with a locale\r\n2. Run `:call nvim_set_option('statusline', '%$')`\r\n3. The `E539` error message is translated\r\n4. Run `:call nvim_set_option('statusline', '%{')`\r\n5. The `E540` error message is not translated\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFailure to set an option from API is either always translated or never translated\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nFailure to set an option from API is sometimes translated but sometimes not",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "should be never translated. API errors (and messages) should be stable.\r\n\r\nNote that \"stable error messages\" is currently not part of `:help api-contract` because we haven't built a good mechanism for standard error messages (i.e. a table of messages and validation functions). Once we do that, it becomes part of the contract.",
